						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Amṛitēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Ballāḷa II.</p>						

						<p>The inscription belongs to the reign of Vīra-Ballāḷa II. It describes the subordinate chief <hi rend="italic">Maṇḍalika</hi> Bāchaṇa who was governing the tract from the <hi rend="italic">rājadhāni-paṭṭaṇa</hi> Aṇṇigeṟe. The purpose of the record seems to be to register a gift to the god Amṛitēśvara. The epigraph being badly damaged and worn out, most of the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
